<node COLOR="#111111" CREATED="1474518399277" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_271682351" MODIFIED="1545118744016" TEXT="Dsquery&#xa;Queries the directory by using search criteria that you specify. ">
<node COLOR="#111111" CREATED="1474511539643" ID="ID_548291390" MODIFIED="1474809472312" TEXT="dsquery computer - finds computers in the directory.&#xa;dsquery contact - finds contacts in the directory.&#xa;dsquery subnet - finds subnets in the directory.&#xa;dsquery group - finds groups in the directory.&#xa;dsquery ou - finds organizational units in the directory.&#xa;dsquery site - finds sites in the directory.&#xa;dsquery server - finds domain controllers in the directory.&#xa;dsquery user - finds users in the directory.&#xa;dsquery quota - finds quota specifications in the directory.&#xa;dsquery partition - finds partitions in the directory.&#xa;dsquery * - finds any object in the directory by using a generic LDAP query.&#xa;&#xa;&#x67e5;&#x8be2;&#x8ba1;&#x7b97;&#x673a;&#x540d;&#x5b57;&#x5305;&#x542b;VM&#x7684;&#x673a;&#x5668;&#xff08;&#x9ed8;&#x8ba4;&#x662f;&#x4ece;domainroot&#x8282;&#x70b9;&#x5f00;&#x59cb;&#x641c;&#x7d22;&#xff09;&#xa;dsquery computer domainroot -limit 0 -o samid -name *VM*&#xa;&#x67e5;&#x627e;&#x57df;&#x63a7;&#x5236;&#x5668;&#xff08;&#x53cb;&#x597d;&#x540d;&#x5b57;&#x663e;&#x793a;&#xff09;&#xa;dsquery server -o rdn -forest &#xa;&#x5728;&#x7ec4;&#x7ec7;&#x5355;&#x5143;Test&#x4e2d;&#x67e5;&#x8be2;&#x4ee5;jon&#x5f00;&#x5934;&#x7684;&#x7528;&#x6237;&#xa;dsquery user OU=Test,DC=Contoso,DC=Com -o upn -name jon*&#xa;&#xa;Maybe this link could hellp you:&#xa;https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/cc732952%28v=ws.11%29.aspx"/>
</node>
<node COLOR="#111111" CREATED="1474601322828" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1011436575" MODIFIED="1474809850121" TEXT="Dsget (&#x8fd9;&#x662f;&#x4e00;&#x4e2a;&#x5f88;&#x7528;&#x7528;&#x7684;&#x547d;&#x4ee4;&#xff0c;&#x67e5;&#x8be2;&#x57df;&#x7c7b;&#x8d44;&#x6e90;&#x5c5e;&#x6027;&#x4fe1;&#x606f;&#xff0c;&#x6bd4;&#x5982;&#x63cf;&#x8ff0;&#x4fe1;&#x606f;)&#xa;Displays the selected properties of a specific object in the directory.">
<node COLOR="#111111" CREATED="1474601337204" ID="ID_918904358" MODIFIED="1474809472314" TEXT="dsget computer - displays properties of computers in the directory.&#xa;dsget contact - displays properties of contacts in the directory.&#xa;dsget subnet - displays properties of subnets in the directory.&#xa;dsget group - displays properties of groups in the directory.&#xa;dsget ou - displays properties of ou&apos;s in the directory.&#xa;dsget server - displays properties of servers in the directory.&#xa;dsget site - displays properties of sites in the directory.&#xa;dsget user - displays properties of users in the directory.&#xa;dsget quota - displays properties of quotas in the directory.&#xa;dsget partition - displays properties of partitions in the directory.&#xa;&#xa;dsquery computer -name *VM* | dsget computer -desc -c&#xa;dsquery user  -limit 0 | dsget user  -samid -display -email -desc -disabled -mgr -c&#xa;dsquery computer -limit 0 | dsget computer -samid -desc -c  &gt; C:\dsget_pc.csv&#xa;&#xa;https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/cc755162%28v=ws.11%29.aspx"/>
</node>
